SkyComment: Nights are bright in Juneau during the summer, even during the darkest part of the night (about 1 AM local time).  While there was light pollution from the Mendenhall Valley and Lemon Creek, the glow in the sky to the north drowned it out.  The dimmest star I could see was Megrez in the Big Dipper using averted vision.  In Bootes, only Arcturus and one of the upper stars were visible (clouds).
LocationComment: I was at the False Outer Point parking lot.  The island blocks much of the southern sky, but there is a good view to the north, east, and west.  Trees block part of the horizon to the west, but not much more than that.  The main issue is vehicle headlights as this location is by the road and there were people there hoping to see the aurora at the time.

I went to Willard Park for this observation and sat outside for a while so my eyes could really adjust. This helped me see a lot more constellations and stars. The sky was clear so there weren't any clouds to obstruct the view. The light pollution wasn't too bad once my eyes adjusted since it is pretty far from any bright lights. I was even able to see a shooting star.

It was a little cloudy again so it was a little hard to see the stars completely. I was still able to see some of the stars. Since I was at my apartment and not super close to any really bright lights, I felt that the light pollution wasn't too terrible but the clouds did make it a little bit harder to see.

SkyComment: Osservazione orientata verso Sud-est, ma anche oggi, nonostante il cielo fosse sereno e sgombro, non sono riuscito a distinguer con chiarezza alcuni astri della costellazione del Leone. Tale senso di non nitidezza della volta celeste è dovuto allo Sekyglow e all’inquinamento luminoso che ne consegue.
LocationComment: Sito rurale di campagna, con presenza di numerose fonti di luce dovute all’illuminazione stradale e a faretti, lampioni e lanterne da esterno, in prossimità di vegetazione di vario tipo.

SkyComment: Some cloud coverage in the night sky as it rained the night before. But with the wind, the clouds were disappearing as time went on.

SkyComment: Nonostante il cielo fosse sgombro e privo di nuvole non sono riuscito a distinguere con chiarezza proprio tutti gli astri della costellazione del Leone. Nell’osservazione ho avuto un senso di non nitidezza, come se il cielo fosse sgranato o sfocato, il così detto fenomeno Skyglow, provocato dalla luce diffusa e non proiettata proveniente soprattutto da Nord-est in corrispondenza della città.
LocationComment: Sito rurale suburbano con presenza di fonti di luce schermata o diffusa, dovute all’illuminazione stradale o ai lampioni e faretti da esterno delle abitazioni vicine. Ho compiuto le osservazioni nel punto più buio possibile del giardino di casa mia, con presenza di alberi.

SkyComment: Il cielo era abbastanza sgombro, con presenza di poche nuvole (1/4 del cielo)  in direzione Sud-est. Presenza di Skyglow o cappa luminosa che fa vedere il cielo sgranato a causa dell’aumento delle fonti di luce diffusa, proveniente soprattutto da Nord-est, in corrispondenza della città (Prato e dintorni).Nel complesso sono riuscito a distinguere abbastanza bene la costellazione del Leone.
LocationComment: Osservazioni compiute a partire da un sito rurale suburbano, con presenza di fonti di luce dovute ad impianti da esterno come faretti, lampioni, lanterne schermati in una precisa direzione e non schermati. Dato che le osservazioni sono state compiute nel giardino dell’abitazione, è presente anche una copertura naturale dovuta agli alberi.

SkyComment: I found that the sky was slightly more cloud-covered but also much clearer at points. The clouds passed after a little while and I was able to see the sky very clearly. I found the mag to be slightly higher than the previous time I viewed the sky due to the fact that I could just see more of the constellation and the stars associated with it.
LocationComment: I found this spot to be perfect for viewing the sky. I faced southwest at the center of the tennis courts looking out towards the soccer fields. I found that facing this way there was nearly 0 light pollution due to the fact that the street lamps were few and behind me.

SkyComment: For the sky conditions, I thought it was pretty clear with the occasional cloud that would move out of the way given a little time. I found that it was slightly hard to adjust to the sky and ended up staying outside an extra 15 minutes just to try to get adjusted. I was not sure if that was from the street lights however or that the sky was just not as clear that night.
LocationComment: I would say that this location was pretty good however not great. I chose to go at the fifty-yard line of the football practice field on the side closer to the stadium. I wanted to go inside the stadium for pitch black surrounding however unfortunately they lock the stadium. I would say that there was not a lot of light pollution and it really only came from the street lights on the other side.

SkyComment: I found that the clouds tonight were slightly worse than the previous night however the sky was much clearer at times. While waiting for the cloud to move I was able to spot the big dipper I believe which was very cool. When the clouds did move I was pretty clearly able to see Denebola and the surrounding stars. I thought I was able to get a pretty good picture of the constellation after looking.
LocationComment: While looking SW from the tennis courts it was incredibly easy to get my eyes adjusted due to the fact there were minimal lights blocking my view. I started on the far side of the courts however after locating the constellation Leo I chose to move towards the center in order to get a better angle(there were some tall trees a little in my way).

SkyComment: CC - Sky was completely clear. I did not see one cloud in the sky from my viewing point. In terms of what I saw in the sky, I saw the constellation Orion, tonight from the SouthWest direction. In addition, I believe I saw the constellation Gemini, specifically what I think was the star Alhena on the bottom of Gemini, was very visible. I also saw Gemini in the SouthWest direction, like I did Orion.
LocationComment: CC - Tonight, I viewed the sky from my back porch, with my back porch light turned off to improve visibility. The only lights in my vicinity were a street lamp down the road from my house, and my neighbors back porch light. Despite these lights contributing to light pollution, I had a nice clear view of the sky tonight.

SkyComment: CC - Tonight, the majority of the sky was covered with clouds, around 80% coverage. Thus, I could see very few stars. I saw about 3 or 4 in total, all to the West, where it was the most clear. The Southern, Eastern, and Northern directions were all majority cloud covered, so could not see any stars in those directions. I could not make out what constellation the stars in the West were from.
LocationComment: CC - I viewed the sky from my backyard with no lights on. There is a street lamp on my street, but from my backyard my house blocks a lot of the light, so I had a better view tonight versus the first night because I viewed the sky from my front yard last night, which has a worse angle to the light post on my street.

No definite starlight peeked through the clouds; however, I saw more white specks, which I concur are stars, than the previous night of observation. As of this moment, there was no skyglow but more light trespass from my neighbor's houses adjacent to mine. Walking further down the neighborhood yields similar observations, with, more emission of bright yellowish hue lighting from increasingly more homes.

SkyComment: Era noche de luna nueva, con la nebulosa de orion en el cenit. Con una leve nuvosidad al norte.
LocationComment: SOL MUISCA,Territorio Ancestral, se encuentra en Colombia, departamento de Boyaca en zona rural a 5 kms de el municipio de villa de leyva, sector lejos de grandes ciudades, con bajos niveles de contaminacion luminica, presenta unos de los cielos más despejados y de baja nuvosidad en colombia, parte del territorio pertenece a un ecosistema denominado bosque seco, el que comunmente relacionamos con zona desertica. Sol Muisca en un conjunto de alojamientos y casas rurales, con 7 unidades, desarrolla actividades de Astroturismo desde el año 2018 y es centro de interpretacion de la cultura ancestral Muisca ( la zona en que se encuentra es zona arqueologica y en el que se encuentran vestigios de calendarios solares y pueden datar de los 1.000 años AC), mantiene un control de luminarias y proteccion de cielos oscuros, registros con equipo y medición de cielos, modelo SQM-L Unit S/N: 8237 (elemento proporcionado por la universidad Distrital de Colombia), registra promedio de 20.45.  El destino Villa de leyva en colombia, es uno de los más demandados por turistas nacionales y extranjeros por su valor; ancestral, paleontologico y colonial.

SkyComment: Clear sky after one month of cloudiness! Good transparency, no moon. Light pollution dome in the west from the city of Leuven. Zenith, south and east are considerably darker. North is partially obscured by houses. South and south-east sky is partially obscured by a forested hill. Observation from backyard with the house shielding street lanterns. I estimate the sky quality as Bortle 5. Finally, comet C/2022 E3 ZTF was an easy object in 10x50 binoculars, but not visible to the naked eye.
LocationComment: Sub-urban.
